    • Method Detail

      • moveToProducer

        void moveToProducer(Producer producer)
        Moves this Agency Payment from the producer it is currently targeting to a new producer. Does the following: 1. Reverses this payment 2. Creates a new AgencyMoneyReceived with the same credential information as this payment and targets it against another producer

        Note that the newly created payment will not be distributed/will not target any specific statement but instead will simply be received against the new target producer

        Parameters:
        producer - the target producer to whom the payment is being moved

      • getAgencyPaymentItems

        java.util.List<AgencyPaymentItem> getAgencyPaymentItems()
        The data model is set up such that AgencyCycleDist (the super class of AgencyCyclePayment) has an array of AgencyDistItem elements (the superclass of AgencyPaymentItem). This method just gets all the elements out of the AgencyDistItems array and casts each one to AgencyPaymentItem and puts them all in a list and returns it.
        Returns:
        list of all AgencyPaymentItem elements on this payment

      • payFromSuspenseItems

        AgencyCyclePayment payFromSuspenseItems(BaseSuspDistItem[] suspPmntItems,
                                      InvoiceItem[] invoiceItems,
                                      AgencyCycleDistPrefill prefill,
                                      DistItemDisposition disposition,
                                      Bundle bundle)
        CC-45513: Release the suspense payment items, and then create a new Modifying Agency Payment with new agency payment items to pay each of the statement items with the given prefill options. All the suspense payment items have to belong to the current agency payment. None of the statement items should have already been paid on this Agency Payment
        Parameters:
        suspPmntItems - The Suspense Payment Items we are going to release in order to get the funds to pay the statement items. Cannot be empty
        invoiceItems - The invoice items we wish to pay from the funds in the supsense items. Cannot be empty
        prefill - prefill option for how we want to pay the statement items
        disposition - The disposition to use for the newly created AgencyDistItems
        bundle - The bundle to create the Modifying Payment in
        Returns:
        the (unexecuted) modifying payment with the new payment items for the given statment items added.
